title: Grateful Dead Live at Sacramento Memorial Auditorium on 1972-08-12
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Sugaree, Me & My Uncle, Bird Song, Black Throated Wind, Deal, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, Playin' In The Band, Big Railroad Blues, Cumberland Blues, Stella Blue, Jack Straw, Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told, Ramble On Rose, Beat It On Down The Line, He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> The Other One-> Truckin', Mississippi Half Step, Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
47 years and still fresh Not a single comment in over nine years? That's wrong. I'm hear -spelling pun intended- to fix that.
This is a terrific master of the soundboard coupled with a strong performance from the summer of 1972. 
The band is rested and confident (and oh so young), in a way you can hear on every song. This is towards the beginning of a five month run that ended in mid-December, during which they established themselves as easily the best band on the planet over that interval.

Another review All those years, and now 2 reviews back to back.

This one is an excellent listen!
